In this chalk-talk video, we learn about how variables are laid out in memory inside your computer, and how expressions and assignment
change variable values as the program executes.
<pre>
  "use strict";
  function myMain() {
     var num;
     var foo = 5;
     num = foo * 2;
     foo = foo - 1;
     num = num + (foo * 2);
     alert(num); 
  }

  myMain();
</pre>
