In this chalk-talk video, we learn more about how variables are laid out in memory inside your computer when an executing function (like myMain)
calls another function to help get the work done.  We learn about having multiple memory maps active; we learn about how information is
passed from the calling memory map to the called one (passing parameters); we learn how information is passed from the called memory map
back to the calling code (on a return).
<pre>
  function myMain() {
     var MAX  = 4;
     var result = fact( MAX );
     alert(result);
  }

  function fact ( N ) {
     var i;
     var prod = 1;
     i = 1;
     while (i<=N) {
        prod = prod * i;
        i++;
     }
     return prod;
  }

  myMain();
</pre>

