problems.text:
In this chalk-talk video, we learn about how variables are laid out in memory inside your computer when several functions are involved.
We see how parameters are transmitted to a called function, and how return values are sent back to the calling code.
We complicate earlier examples of this by having one of the function a "recursive" function... meaning the definition of the function
contains a call to itself.  We illustrate multiple memory maps being active for different calls to the same recursive function,
and we reinforce the idea that function calls execute returns in the reverse of the order in which they are called.
<pre>
  function myMain() {
     var MAX = 4;
     var result = fact( MAX );
     alert(result);
  }

  function fact ( n ) {
     if ( n===1 ) { return 1; }
     var res;
     res = n * fact( n-1 );
     return res;
  }

  myMain();
</pre>
